BGP Attibute Filter
 - This feature allows for updates to be "treat-as-withdraw" that contain specific path attributes.  The prefixes 
   contained in the update will be removed from the routing table.
 - The feature also allows for specific path attributes to be discarded or dropped from updates.  The rest of the 
   update is then processed as usual.
 - Configuring path attributes to either be treat-as-withdraw or discarded will trigger an inbound Route Refresh.
 - This feature is intended to prevent or resolving issues with peer sessions flapping due to the use of new or 
   custom path attributes that are not supported on the receiving peer.
 - The following path attributes cannot be configured for treat-as-withdraw or discard:
   - Type 1 - ORIGIN
   - Type 2 - AS_PATH
   - Type 3 - NEXT_HOP
   - Type 4 - MULTI_EXIT_DISC
   - Type 8 - COMMUNITIES
   - Type 14 - MP_REACH_NLRI
   - Type 15 - MP_UNREACH_NLRI
   - Type 16 - EXTENDED_COMMUNITIES
 - The following path attributes can be configured for treat-as-withdraw or discard for eBGP neighbors only:
   - Type 5 - LOCAL_PREF
   - Type 9 - ORIGINATOR_ID
   - Type 10 - CLUSTER_LIST (Documentation says CLUSTER_ID)

